endent]]\n|align=\"right\"|241\n|align=\"right\"|0.19%\n|\n|- \n|align=\"left\"|{{sortname|G\u00f6l\u00f6k Z.|Buday|nolink=1}}\n|style=\"background:gainsboro;\"|\n|align=\"left\"|[[Independent (politician)|Independent]]\n|align=\"right\"|172\n|align=\"right\"|0.14%\n|\n|- \n|align=\"left\"|{{sortname|Menard D.|Caissey|nolink=1}}\n|style=\"background:gainsboro;\"|\n|align=\"left\"|[[Independent (politician)|Independent]]\n|align=\"right\"|137\n|align=\"right\"|0.11%\n|\n|- \n|align=\"left\"|{{sortname|N. Bur|Maxwell|nolink=1}}\n|style=\"background:gainsboro;\"|\n|align=\"left\"|[[Independent (politician)|Independent]]\n|align=\"right\"|125\n|align=\"right\"|0.10%\n|\n|}\n\n===City councillors===\nTen councillors were elected out of 32 candidates. Of the candidates, 24 were affiliated with a political party, and eight were independent. Eight incumbent councillors were seeking re-election: four from [[Vision Vancouver]], three from the [[Non-Partisan Association|NPA]], and one from [[Coalition of Progressive Electors|COPE]]. Of the elected councillors, seven were from Vision Vancouver, two from COPE and one from the NPA.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:5px; width: 60%\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:20%;\"|Candidate name\n! style=\"width:0.05%;\"|\n! style=\"width:30%;\"| Party affiliation\n! style=\"width:8%;\"|Votes\n! style=\"width:5%;\"|% of votes\n! style=\"width:5%;\"|Elected\n|- \n|align=\"left\"|('''I''') {{sortname|Raymond|Louie}}\n|style=\"background:#003399;\"|\n|align=\"left\"|[[Vision Vancouver]]\n|align=\"right\"|66,226\n|align=\"right\"|53.29%\n|'''X'''\n|- \n|align=\"left\"|('''I''') {{sortname|Heather|Deal}}\n|style=\"background:#003399;\"|\n|align=\"left\"|[[Vision Vancouver]]\n|align=\"right\"|63,116\n|align=\"right\"|50.78%\n|'''X'''\n|- \n|align=\"left\"|('''I''') {{sortname|George|Chow}}\n|style=\"background:#003399;\"|\n|align=\"left\"|[[Vision Vancouver]]\n|align=\"right\"|62,262\n|align=\"right\"|50.10%\n|'''X'''\n|- \