000\n*Street Lighting, Traffic Signal, and Communications Systems at $14,660,000\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:right; margin:5px; width: 30%\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:80%;\"|Option\n! style=\"width:10%;\"|Votes\n! style=\"width:10%;\"|Percentage\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''Yes'''\n|'''78,506'''\n|'''63.16%'''\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|No\n|28,024\n|36.84%\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''''Total Votes'''\n|'''''124,285'''''\n|'''''100%'''''\n|}\n\n====Public safety and civic facilities====\n2. Are you in favour of Council having the authority, without further assent of the electors, to pass by-laws between January 1, 2009, and December 31, 2011, to borrow an aggregate $68,605,000 for the following purposes?\n*Public Safety at $31,965,000\n*Civic Facilities at $32,490,000\n*Library at $4,150,000\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:right; margin:5px; width: 30%\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:80%;\"|Option\n! style=\"width:10%;\"|Votes\n! style=\"width:10%;\"|Percentage\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''Yes'''\n|'''79,429'''\n|'''63.91%'''\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|No\n|26,679\n|36.09%\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''''Total Votes'''\n|'''''124,285'''''\n|'''''100%'''''\n|}\n\n====Parks and recreation facilities====\n3. Are you in favour of Council having the authority, without further assent of the electors, to pass by-laws between January 1, 2009, and December 31, 2011, to borrow an aggregate $59,575,000 for the following purposes?\n*Recreation Facilities at $52,247,000\n*Parks at $7,328,000\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:right; margin:5px; width: 30%\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:80%;\"|Option\n! style=\"width:10%;\"|Votes\n! style=\"width:10%;\"|Percentage\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''Yes'''\n|'''77,259'''\n|'''62.16%'''\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|No\n|29,366\n|37.84%\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''''Total Votes'''\n|'''''124,285'''''\n|'''''100%'''''\n|}\n\n==Voter and party statistics==\n===Voter turnout===\nOf the 403,663 registered voters, there were 124,285 recorded ballots, marking the voter turnout at 30.79%. This is an decrease of 1.66% from the 32.45% turnout during the [[2005 Vancouver municipal election|previous municipal election]] in 2005.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://former.vancouver.ca/ctyclerk/election2005/finalresults.htm |title=Election summary - Election 2005 - City of Vancouver Elections| publisher=City of Vancouver| accessdate=July 27, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Elected percentage by party===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:5px\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:0.05%;\"|\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:30%;\"|Party\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10%;|Mayor\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10%;|Councillors\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10%;|Park Board commissioners\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10%;|School Board trustees\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10%;|Total candidates\n|-\n|- bgcolor=#fcfcfc\n|align=\"center\"|'''# Elected'''\n|align=\"center\"|'''% Elected'''\n|align=\"center\"|'''# Elected'''\n|align=\"center\"|'''% Elected'''\n|align=\"center\"|'''# Elected'''\n|align=\"center\"|'''% Elected'''\n|align=\"center\"|'''# Elected'''\n|align=\"center\"|'''% Elected'''\n|align=\"center\"|'''# Elected'''\n|align=\"center\"|'''% Elected'''\n|- \n|style=\"background:#2F873E;\"|\n|align=\"left\"|[[Green Party of Vancouver]]\n|align=\"right\"|''NIL''\n|align=\"right\"|''N/A''\n|align=\"right\"|''NIL''\n|align=\"right\"|''N/A''\n|align=\"right\"|1/1\n|align=\"right\"|100.0%\n|align=\"right\"|''NIL''\n|align=\"right\"|''N/A''\n|align=\"right\"|'''1/1'''\n|align=\"right\"|'''100.0%'''\n|- \n|style=\"background:#003399;\"|\n|align=\"left\"|[[Vision Vancouver]]\n|align=\"right\"|1/1\n|align=\"right\"|100.0%\n|align=\"right\"|7/8\n|align=\"right\"|87.5%\n|align=\"right\"|4/4\n|align=\"right\"|100.0%\n|align=\"right\"|4/4\n|align=\"right\"|100.0%\n|align=\"right\"|'''16/17'''\n|align=\"right\"|'''94.1%'''\n|- \n|style=\"background:#FFCC00;\"|\n|align=\"left\"|[[Coalition of Progressive Electors]]\n|align=\"right\"|''NIL''\n|align=\"right\"|''